doc.ContractDescription: A MARS ATMOSPHERE AND AEROSOL REANALYSIS. ENSEMBLE DATA ASSIMILATION OPTIMALLY COMBINES SPACECRAFT OBSERVATIONS WITH SHORT TERM FORECASTS FROM AN ATMOSPHERIC MODEL, ENABLING THE CONSTRUCTION OF A COMPLETE SET OF SYNOPTIC MAPS OF MARTIAN ATMOSPHERIC CONDITIONS TEMPERATURE, WINDS, AND SURFACE PRESSURE AND THEIR UNCERTAINTIES. FUNDED BY MDAP, OVER THE PAST SEVERAL YEARS OUR TEAM AT UMD, GFDL, AND AER HAS PRODUCED AND EVALUATED A MULTI- YEAR REANALYSIS OF TES AND MCS TEMPERATURE OBSERVATIONS GREYBUSH ET AL. 2012. WE HAVE EXAMINED TRAVELING WAVES GREYBUSH ET AL., 2013B, THERMAL TIDES ZHAO ET AL., 2013, AND ATMOSPHERIC PREDICTABILITY GREYBUSH ET AL., 2013A. WE HAVE ALSO IMPROVED OUR TECHNIQUES FOR EFFECTIVE USE OF MARS SPACECRAFT OBSERVATIONS IN OUR ASSIMILATION SYSTEM, INCLUDING A PATHWAY TO INTERACTIVE RETRIEVALS WITH FORECASTS FROM ASSIMILATION USED AS THE PRIOR; HOFFMAN 2010 USING THE OSS SYSTEM FOR TES ELUSZKIEWICZ ET AL., 2008; HOFFMAN ET AL., 2012, AND THE DEVELOPMENT OF AN MCS FORWARD MODEL. WE SEEK TO CONTINUE OUR SUCCESSFUL PROGRAM BY FOCUSING ON THE ANALYSIS OF MARTIAN ATMOSPHERIC AEROSOLS, AND THE BIGGEST CHALLENGE IN MARTIAN METEOROLOGY, THE GENESIS AND EVOLUTION OF DUST STORMS. WE EMPHASIZE THAT AN IMPROVED DEPICTION OF AEROSOL HORIZONTAL, VERTICAL, AND TEMPORAL DISTRIBUTIONS, AND THEREFORE HEATING RATES, WILL ALSO IMPROVE THE ATMOSPHERIC STATE IN THE REANALYSIS, AND SUBSEQUENT FORECASTS. THE REANALYSIS WILL USE ALL AVAILABLE OBSERVATIONS FROM TES NADIR AND LIMB AND MCS, AND THE BEST AVAILABLE ASSIMILATION SYSTEM STARTING FROM RETRIEVALS, AND MOVING TO INTERACTIVE RETRIEVALS AND RADIANCES. WE WILL USE ENSEMBLE DATA ASSIMILATION THE LETKF TO ESTIMATE AEROSOL PROPERTIES E.G., SIZE DISTRIBUTIONS, STRENGTH OF RADIATIVELY ACTIVE WATER ICE CLOUDS AND SURFACE FLUXES. THE LETKF CAN TAKE ADVANTAGE OF THE ERROR COVARIANCES BETWEEN ATMOSPHERIC AEROSOL, TEMPERATURE AND SURFACE BRIGHTNESS TEMPERATURE FIELDS, LEADING TO A COMPREHENSIVE ASSIMILATION DATA SET DESPITE THE LIMITATIONS IN OBSERVATIONAL COVERAGE AND IMPERFECT MODEL PHYSICS. PARAMETER ESTIMATION WILL BE USED TO IMPROVE THE MODEL DUST LIFTING AND SEDIMENTATION AND THUS INCREASE OUR ABILITY TO SIMULATE AND PREDICT DUST STORMS.
